const vop = `<h2>General terms and conditions and personal data protection principles (GDPR) “Piano Terminal”</h2>
      <h4>GENERAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS AND PERSONAL DATA PROTECTION PRINCIPLES (GDPR)</h4>
      <p>“Piano Terminal”</p>
      <p>Welcome to Piano Payments! We are very glad that you have chosen our Piano Terminal for your business. We have drawn up these General Terms and Conditions (hereinafter the „ GTC “) with the aim of creating a fair and partnership-based environment between Piano Payments s.r.o. , IČ: 066 78 815, with its registered office at Thámova 18, 18600, Praha 8 - Karlín, hereinafter „ we “ or the „ Company “) and you (hereinafter „ you “ or the „ customer “).</p>
      <p>We want to help you grow and improve your business with our products. Therefore, do not take these conditions as a list of prohibitions and obligations, but rather as rules we have agreed on so that our cooperation works over the long term to the satisfaction of both parties.</p>
      <p>As a payment institution we are subject to strict regulations and are a so-called obliged entity, which means that some of our services (including payment services) are regulated . Before you can start using the Piano Terminal to the full and accepting payments through it, we must therefore first properly verify you and your business in accordance with anti-money-laundering (AML) laws.</p>
      <p>We know that administrative procedures can sometimes be lengthy, especially in today's digital sphere. During this AML/KYC screening we will probably need you to provide certain documents and answer supplementary questions about your business. But there is nothing to worry about – our trained sales representatives and colleagues from customer support are here to help you, and together we will go through this process as smoothly as possible .</p>
      <p>We would also like to prepare you straight away for the fact that these legal obligations apply on an ongoing basis. This means that we will have to come to you with a similar range of questions and a request to update documents in the future too . However, we will always try to make the whole process as simple and automated for you as possible, so that it does not cause you unnecessary trouble beyond the usual and strictly necessary extent.</p>
      <p>We can hand over the device or selected accessories to you in two ways, exactly according to what we have agreed in your contract:</p>
      <p>A. Purchase of hardware If you decide to purchase the selected accessories, they become your property at the moment we deliver them to you. The standard warranty covers defects in materials and workmanship under normal use.</p>
      <p>B. Rental / Loan of hardware If you rent or borrow the terminal from us, it remains our property and we entrust it to you for the entire duration of our cooperation. Please protect it from damage and carry out its routine maintenance. Naturally, you must not sell the terminal, lend it to anyone else, or use it (without our prior consent) for any other purpose or anywhere other than at your premises defined in the contract. If our paths diverge and we terminate the contract, you simply return the device to us again.</p>
      <p>You will find more detail in Annex No. 1 to these GTC .</p>
      <p>The Piano Terminal is a sophisticated and smart device that will become the heart of your payments. However, in order for it to serve you reliably and flawlessly for as long and as well as possible, it requires basic care, reasonable handling and protection from damage on your part.</p>
      <p>But we are in this with you – if, despite that, anything happens to the terminal or it stops working as it should, we will not leave you in the lurch. For the sake of clarity, we have set out all the rules for resolving any technical hitches, the guarantees and details of what we are liable for in a separate Annex No. 2 to these GTC , which governs these situations in detail,</p>
      <p>If you were to conclude that the conditions for a complaint regarding the Piano Terminal (or its operation) have been met, do not hesitate to use our complaints procedure , which is Annex No. 3 to these GTC .</p>
      <p>So that your work goes smoothly, it matters which system we connect the terminal to:</p>
      <ul><li>Connection to POS systems from the Piano Group: This is the smoothest path. The terminal is fully integrated with our POS systems. As soon as you ring up a sale, the amount is sent straight to the terminal, so you will no longer have to slow things down by re-entering it manually . Here we can fully guarantee that everything will run perfectly.</li><li>Connection to other POS systems: Here too we will accommodate you, but if you use software outside our group, unfortunately we cannot fully guarantee the flawless communication of the two systems, nor any errors should you have to enter amounts manually.</li><li>Mobile waiter (Full integration): For this special variant you will have both the POS and the payment application in one handy device (the Piano Terminal). For everything to work securely, please use only software approved by us in it and do not interfere with the system in any way.</li></ul>
      <p>For your convenience, we have equipped every Piano Terminal with its own data SIM card (which remains our property). We want you to use our services exactly for what they are intended – that is, for the trouble-free acceptance of payments and the operation of our applications inside the Piano Terminal .</p>
      <p>We kindly ask you never to remove the SIM card from the terminal and not to use it in other devices (such as your mobile phones or routers). We build on mutual trust. If, however, it were to happen that you do not agree with us and misuse the SIM card for other purposes, this damages our cooperation. In such an exceptional case, in order to protect our services, we would be forced to immediately block both the terminal and the SIM card, cancel your warranty on the device and, where appropriate, terminate our contract with immediate effect. But we rely on the fact that, as proper partners, we will respect the rules.</p>
      <p>Since, in our experience, every customer is a little different, and at the same time we want to leave our customers the choice regarding the additional services they will use with the Piano Terminal product. If we agree together and you wish to use certain additional services with the Piano Terminal, it will be just as easy as everything else. We believe that the range of additional services will gradually expand or change, and therefore you will find the current offer in a separate Annex No. 4 to these GTC and the pricing conditions in our Piano Terminal price list .</p>
      <p>The protection and security of your data are extremely important to us. Because we want our communication to be as transparent as possible, we set out how we look after data:</p>
      <ul><li>What we process and why: In order to register and support you, we need to know your company and contact details. At the same time, we must process financial and operational data for the payments themselves and the data necessary for AML verification (identification of owners, etc.), as we mentioned in the introduction.</li><li>Security: We treat your data with the utmost respect and protect it with security measures so that no unauthorised person can access it. Only those employees and partners who genuinely need it for their work have access to it.</li><li>Who sees the data: We sometimes have to share your data with our partners with whom we want, or even must, cooperate. We always do so with regard to your security and applicable legislation.</li><li>Your rights: As our partner, you have the full right to ask us at any time for access to your data, its correction, deletion or to ask us anything regarding its processing. We are fully at your disposal.</li></ul>
      <p>The full wording of the personal data protection principles (privacy notice) forms Annex No. 5 to these GTC .</p>
      <p>The digital and legislative world is constantly changing, so it may happen that our paths diverge. In such a case we will proceed in accordance with Annex No. 6 to these GTC .</p>
      <p>Furthermore, a situation may arise where it will be necessary to supplement or update these GTC or bring them into line with new legislation. Or simply in order to improve our services. Of course, we will always inform you in advance of all such changes so that you know where you stand.</p>
      <p>We look forward to our shared journey and successes with the Piano Terminal, or with other products from the Piano family! Should you have any questions, do not hesitate to contact us – our team is here for you.</p>
      <p>In Prague, on 12 May 2026</p>
      <p>A. Delivery conditions: When taking over the Piano Terminal delivered via a carrier service, the customer is obliged to check the integrity of the packaging and to report any defects to the carrier without delay. If damage to the packaging is discovered indicating unauthorised entry into the consignment, the customer is not obliged to accept the consignment from the carrier. By signing the delivery note / rental note, the customer confirms that the consignment met all requirements and that any later complaint about damaged packaging will not be taken into account. If, for reasons on the customer's side, it is necessary to deliver the device repeatedly or in another manner, the customer undertakes to cover the costs associated with this delivery.</p>
      <p>B. Installation: If the customer chooses “installation at the premises”, such a service includes, in addition to the installation of the Piano Terminal, also the activation of the SIM card and basic training of the staff. Installation also includes connecting the terminal to the POS system, whereby the scope of the connection may vary depending on the brand and type of POS system used by the customer. Installation at the premises is charged according to the current Piano Terminal price list .</p>
      <p>C. Use and licence: The customer is entitled to use the Piano Terminal and the provided software solely for their own needs and only for the purposes for which it is intended. No software product contained in the Piano Terminal (POS system, payment application and add-ons) is the subject of purchase; the customer is provided solely with the right to use it, a so-called licence. The contract, in the part relating to the software product, is concluded at the moment when the customer, after the start of the installation or activation process, accepts the displayed business and licence conditions of the Company.</p>
      <h4>ANNEX No. 2 TO THE GTC: LIABILITY FOR DEFECTS AND WARRANTY</h4>
      <p>A. Scope of the warranty: In the event that the customer purchases the Piano Terminal, the Company provides a warranty on this device for a period of 6 months , which begins to run on the day the customer takes over the device. The warranty applies solely to defects in materials and manufacturing deficiencies discovered during the warranty period. The contracting parties expressly exclude the application of the provisions of Section 1921, Section 1922 and Section 2112 of the Civil Code. The warranty is provided only on the condition that the device is used in accordance with the operating instructions, is not used in an inappropriate manner and the customer duly fulfils its obligations towards the Company. If the customer uses the Piano Terminal under rental or loan and duly fulfils all of its obligations towards the Company, including the timely payment of the agreed fees, the Company provides such a customer with a guarantee of the device's functionality for the entire duration of the relationship.</p>
      <p>B. Warranty exclusions: None of the warranties provided applies to damage caused by improper installation, ingress of liquid into the device, normal wear and tear, mechanical damage, electrical overvoltage or short circuit, or the action of a computer virus. Furthermore, the warranty does not apply to defects caused by the use of illegal or unapproved software, excessive strain in an unsuitable environment (humidity, temperature, dust), unqualified intervention, arbitrary repair by the customer or the action of force majeure.</p>
      <p>C. Method of settlement: If the device is defective, the customer is not entitled to withdraw from the contract or demand a discount on the price, provided that the Company is prepared to remedy the defect or replace the device with a defect-free one and does so within a reasonable time.</p>
      <p>D. Limitation of the Company's liability: The Company is not liable for any harm arising as a result of a breach of the customer's contractual obligations, or where the customer contributed to the occurrence of the harm through its own culpable conduct. The Company is furthermore released from liability for harm arising as a result of circumstances excluding liability, which also include defects in the means of distance communication (e.g. internet connection outages) and failures of technical means not caused by the Company. The Company is also not liable for the delayed delivery of products for objective reasons beyond its control, nor for the functionality of any software that the Company did not itself approve or supply.</p>
      <p>E. Limitation of compensation: The contracting parties have agreed that the Company shall in no case be liable for the customer's lost profit. The Company is not liable for any harm that does not arise in direct connection with a breach of a legal obligation of the Company. The Company's total liability for harm is limited to a maximum of the price for the purchased hardware excluding VAT that the customer paid to the Company for its acquisition.</p>
      <p>F. Customer support: If you need a consultation regarding the functionality of the Piano Terminal, defects or repairs, the customer can contact Piano Customer Support - see www.piano.cz / www.qerko.com</p>
      <p>Complaints procedure of Piano Payments s.r.o. (valid for the Piano Terminal product)</p>
      <p>A. Introductory and basic provisions This complaints procedure governs the manner of communication between the customer (user of the Piano Terminal) and Piano Payments s.r.o. , IČ: 066 78 815, with its registered office at Thámova 18, 18600, Praha 8 - Karlín (hereinafter also the “ Company ”), when submitting complaints or grievances. The complaints procedure applies primarily to the Piano Terminal product and the services associated with it. On new devices that the customer purchases, the Company provides a warranty of 6 months, and on refurbished devices a warranty of 3 months, whereby this period begins to run on the day the customer takes over the device.</p>
      <p>B. Manner and requirements for submitting a complaint The customer may submit a complaint or grievance in one of the following ways:</p>
      <ul><li>In writing or in person at the registered office of Piano Payments s.r.o. at the address Thámova 18, Praha 8 - Karlín.</li><li>By filling in the relevant electronic form available on the page www.qerko.com / www.piano.cz .</li><li>By e-mail or by telephone via the Company's customer support.</li></ul>
      <p>When submitting a complaint it is essential to state:</p>
      <ul><li>The first name and surname of the person submitting the complaint.</li><li>The IČ and name of the company or natural person.</li><li>A contact e-mail and telephone connection for prompt resolution.</li><li>An exact description of the problem, including the submission of available documentation supporting the claim.</li><li>A statement of the claim that the customer is asserting against the Company.</li></ul>
      <p>If a complaint is submitted by an unauthorised person, the necessary supporting documents are missing, or it was submitted after the statutory time limit had expired, the Company has the right to refuse to investigate the complaint.</p>
      <p>C. Delivery of the hardware being complained about If the subject of the complaint is directly the device (Piano Terminal), the customer shall deliver it at their own expense (in person or by post) to the specialised address of the Company's complaints department: Jankovcova 53, Praha 7 - Holešovice . If the customer does not deliver the device being complained about within 14 days of the start of the complaints procedure, the procedure in question will be automatically terminated.</p>
      <p>D. Time limits for asserting a complaint The customer is obliged to assert a complaint without undue delay after discovering the grounds for its submission, but at the latest within 30 days of the situation arising. Exception for payment transactions: If the complaint concerns payment transactions, the customer is obliged to report it at the latest within 13 months of the day on which the transaction in question was or was not carried out. If they fail to do so, their rights fully lapse upon the expiry of the stated time limit.</p>
      <p>E. Warranty limitation (Piano Terminal hardware) The Company does not guarantee that the terminal will meet all of the customer's specific requirements. It is not considered a defect of the device, and the warranty does not apply, in particular in cases where:</p>
      <ul><li>the device is operated on an incorrectly configured computer network;</li><li>the device is used in breach of the operating or business conditions;</li><li>third-party applications that may affect its flawless operation are installed on the terminal;</li><li>the device was damaged by electrical overvoltage, excessive soiling or a natural element.</li><li>The Company may also refuse a complaint in the event that the device is handed over excessively soiled, or without a power adapter.</li></ul>
      <p>F. Course of resolution and settlement of the complaint</p>
      <ul><li>Remote diagnostics: Where the nature of the defect allows it, that is, in particular in cases where it is evident that it is exclusively a software defect, the customer is obliged first to use the option of remote diagnostics, or possibly also the remote repair of the damaged device.</li><li>Hardware defects: After the device is delivered to the Company's complaints department, a service technician will carry out diagnostics. A justified hardware complaint will be resolved without undue delay, at the latest within 30 days of its proper assertion and the delivery of the device. A complaint may be resolved by repair, replacement with a new or refurbished device, or rejection. Replacement is only possible if the customer duly fulfils its obligations towards the Company (e.g. is not in arrears with the payment of any amounts or with the fulfilment of any other material obligations towards the Company).</li><li>Payment services: If the complaint concerns the provision of payment services, the Company will provide a response within 15 working days of receiving the complaint. If an obstacle beyond the Company's control prevents timely settlement, it will inform the customer of this and respond at the latest within 35 working days.</li></ul>
      <p>The customer is notified of the resolution by e-mail or telephone and receives a complaint report. If the customer does not collect an irreparable device within 30 days of the conclusion of the complaint, they consent to its ecological disposal.</p>
      <p>G. Price list of other services related to the complaints procedure In the event of resolving complaints, fees according to the current Piano Terminal price list apply. If the customer fails to duly and in time pay the costs associated with an unjustified complaint, the Company reserves the right to limit or suspend the provision of its services.</p>
      <p>H. Final provisions Piano Payments s.r.o. reserves the right to change this Complaints Procedure on the basis of changes in the legal order or its business policy. Any changes will be announced to customers and published sufficiently in advance, at least 30 days before the day they take effect.</p>
      <p>In Prague, on 12 May 2026</p>
      <p>Additional services (functionalities) are not an automatic part of the Piano Terminal and their activation may be subject to a request by the Customer or the conclusion of a separate contract (amendment). Some additional services (functionalities) are free of charge, some are charged according to the current price list (see the Piano Terminal price list ).</p>
      <ul><li>Mobile waiter: The mobile waiter function enables the entry of items onto bills and work with bills without the need for physical contact with the POS. Activation of the mobile waiter functionality in the Piano Terminal is free of charge upon the Customer's request. The functionality is available only on selected POS systems from the Piano Group. Before activation, the up-to-dateness of the software in the POS system used will be verified.</li><li>Integration with the POS: The POS integration function enables the fast and flawless transfer of amounts to be paid into the Piano Terminal without the need for manual intervention by the staff. The functionality is available only on selected POS systems from the Piano Group. Before activation, the up-to-dateness of the software in the POS system used will be verified.</li><li>Tips: We want to assist you with the Piano Terminal in the simple and efficient collection of tips for your staff. We continuously monitor the current legislation (already at the preparation stage) and will strive to ensure that the Piano Terminal is a good helper to you in its everyday application in this area too, for the entire duration of our relationship. The tips function can be activated in the Piano Terminal free of charge upon the Customer's request.</li></ul>
      <p>A. Who we are and who is the controller of your data Piano Payments s.r.o. , IČ: 066 78 815, with its registered office at Thámova 18, 18600, Praha 8 - Karlín, is in the position of controller in relation to your personal data. The protection of your personal data is a priority for us and we ensure that all processing takes place transparently and in accordance with the applicable legal regulations (primarily the EU GDPR).</p>
      <p>B. What personal data we collect The scope of the data processed depends on the services you use with us. We collect in particular the following categories:</p>
      <ul><li>Identification and contact data: first name, surname, postal address, telephone number, e-mail address.</li><li>Company and business data: company name, IČ, DIČ, registered office address, type of business.</li><li>Financial and transaction data: bank account details, payment card details (card type, last 4 digits, expiry date), information on transactions (volume, currency, date) and billing data.</li><li>Due diligence (KYC) and fraud prevention data: identification documents (identity cards, passports) for verifying identity, information necessary for anti-money-laundering (AML) prevention and account data from credit registers.</li><li>Technical data: IP address, information about the device (names, identifiers), browser types and data on how you interact with our services.</li></ul>
      <p>C. Why we process the data and on what legal basis We use your data only when the law allows us to do so. We process personal data for the following reasons:</p>
      <ul><li>Performance of the contract: we need the data to deliver our payment systems, process payment transactions, maintain your account and send invoices or payment requests.</li><li>Legal obligation: to fulfil obligations arising from accounting regulations and legislation in the area of combating money laundering (AML) and fraud prevention.</li><li>Legitimate interest: to protect our business, detect fraud, carry out analyses to improve services and for direct marketing (sending information about similar products and services).</li><li>Consent: where we send you marketing communications beyond the scope of the legitimate interest or use certain cookies. You can withdraw your consent at any time.</li></ul>
      <p>D. With whom we share your data We fundamentally do not sell your data. We provide access to it only to the extent necessary and under strict security conditions to the following third parties:</p>
      <ul><li>Providers of IT and cloud services (the servers are located primarily in the Czech Republic or the EU).</li><li>Payment card networks (e.g. Visa, Mastercard) and intermediaries for carrying out and settling payments.</li><li>Fraud prevention agencies and credit reference agencies for the purpose of verifying identity and assessing risks.</li><li>Companies from the Piano Group, primarily for the purpose of further improving our products, including technical support.</li><li>Regulatory and public authorities (e.g. the Police of the Czech Republic), where required by legal regulations. If we transfer your data outside the European Economic Area (EEA), we always implement appropriate security safeguards, for example by using standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission.</li></ul>
      <p>E. Data security We have implemented advanced technical and organisational measures to protect your personal data against accidental loss, unauthorised access or alteration. Only employees on the basis of the “need-to-know” principle (only where they need it for their work) have access to the data. We use password encryption, security breach detection systems and antivirus protection.</p>
      <p>F. How long we retain the data We retain personal data solely for the period necessary to fulfil the purposes for which they were obtained. By law we are obliged to retain financial and transaction documentation as a rule for a period of 10 years from the end of the contractual relationship. We keep data for marketing purposes until you tell us that you are no longer interested in such communications (e.g. by withdrawing consent). After the stipulated period has elapsed, we irreversibly destroy or anonymise the data.</p>
      <p>G. Your legal rights In connection with the processing of your personal data, you have the following rights:</p>
      <ul><li>Right of access: you can ask us for a copy of the personal data we process about you.</li><li>Right to rectification: you can request the completion or correction of incorrect and incomplete data.</li><li>Right to erasure (“right to be forgotten”): you have the right to request the deletion of personal data if there is no good reason for their further retention (e.g. a legal obligation).</li><li>Right to restriction of processing: you can request the suspension of processing, for example while we verify the accuracy of the data.</li><li>Right to data portability: you have the right to obtain from us the data you have provided to us, in a structured format, and to pass it on to another provider.</li><li>Right to object: you can object to processing based on our legitimate interest (e.g. to automated decision-making or the sending of advertising offers).</li></ul>
      <p>If you believe that we are not processing your personal data lawfully, you also have the right to address your complaint to the Office for Personal Data Protection.</p>
      <p>H. Subsidiary application of the Company's general personal data protection principles Unless expressly stated otherwise in these GTC or the related contract, the General Personal Data Protection Principles for the Qerko service, which are available at www.qerko.com/legal , also apply to the relationships established by the Contract for the use of the “Piano Terminal” and the provision of related services.</p>
      <p>I. Contact us Should you have any questions or if you wish to exercise your rights, you can contact us in writing at the controller's address: Piano Payments s.r.o., Thámova 18, 18600, Praha 8 - Karlín.</p>
      <p>A. WAYS OF TERMINATING THE CONTRACT</p>
      <p>The contractual relationship established by the Contract can be terminated by written agreement of both contracting parties.</p>
      <p>Either of the contracting parties is entitled to terminate the Contract in writing even without stating a reason . The notice period in such a case is 3 months and begins to run on the first day of the calendar month following the demonstrable delivery of the written notice to the other contracting party.</p>
      <p>B. IMMEDIATE TERMINATION OF THE CONTRACT BY THE COMPANY</p>
      <p>The Company (Piano Payments s.r.o.) reserves the right to unilaterally terminate the Contract without a notice period (to withdraw from the Contract with immediate effect) if the customer is in arrears with the payment of the fee or other charges due to the Company or is repeatedly in arrears with the fulfilment of other material obligations under the Contract and/or the GTC.</p>
      <p>The Company is entitled to proceed to the immediate termination of the Contract on grounds of arrears with the payment of the fee or other charges due to the Company provided that payment of the amount owed cannot be achieved even by automatic payment from the settlement , to which the customer expressed their consent, at the latest by the end of the calendar month following the month in which the customer's arrears arose.</p>
      <p>Given that the Company is the holder of a payment licence of the Czech National Bank, the Company further reserves the right to immediately terminate the contract by written notice to the customer on the grounds of a serious failure by the customer in areas directly related to the licensed (payment) service , in particular in cases of (i) breach of the card payment system rules, (ii) conducting business activity in an unlawful manner or in a manner that raises serious doubts about the sustainability of such business activity, (iii) conducting business activity in a manner that damages the good reputation or relationships not only of the operator of such activity, but also of the partners of the entity conducting such business activity or conducting its business activity in such a manner, (iv) fraudulent or other similar undesirable activities of the Customer, (v) or at the request of the card payment system, the intermediary (acquirer) or the payment service provider.</p>
      <p>The customer is furthermore obliged to duly comply with the PCI DSS standards and, in the event of suspicion of a data leak, fraud or other security incident, to provide the Company, the acquirer or the card schemes with full cooperation in the investigation or audit.</p>
      <p>The customer further undertakes not to carry out illegal or prohibited transactions , including any activities supporting money laundering or the financing of terrorism, or activities that are directly or indirectly related to money laundering, trading in illegal goods or the circumvention of sanctions.</p>
      <p>The Company may also immediately terminate the contract with the customer in the event that the business activity and/or the persons in the ownership structure or acting on behalf of the customer are not in accordance with the Company's internal directives in the area of AML/KYC .</p>
      <p>The customer acknowledges that the card schemes (e.g. Visa, Mastercard) may at any time suspend or terminate their participation in the event of a breach of their rules . If the volume of transactions processed by the Customer reaches the limit set by the card schemes or the acquirer (e.g. USD 1 million for Visa / USD 10 million for Mastercard), the customer may be asked to conclude a direct acquisition contract with the acquirer. The customer fully understands that in the event of the occurrence of the above circumstances the contract will be terminated immediately and the customer will be obliged to take all measures to remedy the situation that has arisen and to minimise damage.</p>
      <p>C. ADDITIONAL FEE PAYABLE TO THE COMPANY FOR EARLY TERMINATION</p>
      <p>If the Contract is unilaterally terminated by the Company pursuant to part B. of this annex (i.e. on grounds of non-payment of the fee or the customer's arrears with the fulfilment of other material obligations) and this occurs earlier than 24 months from the conclusion of the Contract , the Company becomes entitled to an additional fee.</p>
      <p>D. RETURN OF THE DEVICE (RIGHT OF UNINSTALLATION)</p>
      <p>Unless expressly agreed otherwise by the contracting parties, a customer who did not purchase the device (Piano Terminal) into their ownership (i.e. held it under rental or loan) undertakes to return all such rented (borrowed) hardware to the Company at the latest within 20 working days after the end of the cooperation, either in person or by post to the address of the Company's complaints department: Jankovcova 53, Praha 7 - Holešovice.</p>
      <p>If the customer's stated obligation is not duly fulfilled, the Company is entitled to carry out the uninstallation of the device directly on the premises of the customer's establishment. For this purpose the customer expresses their unconditional consent to an authorised representative of the Company (technician) entering the premises during normal opening hours for the purpose of uninstalling the device and transporting it away. The fees associated with the uninstallation under this article are governed by the current Piano Terminal price list .</p>
      <p>The contracting parties expressly agree that payment of the stated uninstallation fee does not affect the Company's right to compensation for any harm (damage) caused to it in connection with the uninstallation or the delayed return of the borrowed device.</p>
      <p>E. PENALTIES FOR DAMAGE, NON-RETURN OR DESTRUCTION OF THE DEVICE</p>
      <p>In the event that the customer, upon termination of the Contract, returns the device visibly damaged or excessively worn, the Company will impose on them a penalty corresponding to the extent of the damage or wear up to the amount of the device's acquisition price. In the case of minor damage , which does not limit the usability of the device for another customer, the penalty may amount to up to 50 % of the device's acquisition price, and in the case of substantial damage , which requires a fundamental repair or replacement of certain components before the device is used by another customer, the penalty may amount to up to 100 % of the device's acquisition price. If they do not return the borrowed or rented device at all , or if a device that is completely non-functional is returned (uninstalled) to the Company, the customer is obliged to pay the Company a one-off penalty amounting to the acquisition price of the provided device . For the purposes of calculating the acquisition price, which is the basis for determining the penalty for the return of a damaged or destroyed device, the acquisition price will take normal wear and tear into account such that the acquisition price of the device resulting from the current price list will be reduced by 20 % for each completed year in which the device is in the customer's use.</p>`;
